-- ── treble-ai → marketing-seo ───────────────────────────────
('Treble.ai', 'treble-ai', 'AI WhatsApp marketing platform — official Meta BSP partner with chatbots, bulk campaigns, and CRM integration for LATAM brands.', 'Treble.ai is an AI-powered WhatsApp marketing platform built around the Meta WhatsApp Business API for Latin American and Spanish-speaking markets. The product is an official Meta BSP (Business Solution Provider) partner — a status that controls access to bulk-broadcast templates, conversation-API throttling, and verified-business profiles. Drag-and-drop chat-flow builder lets non-technical teams create automated conversation flows; AI chatbots handle FAQs, lead qualification, and conversation summarization; bulk campaign broadcasting sends personalized messages to segmented audiences at scale; live agent handoff transfers to humans when escalation rules fire; native HubSpot and Salesforce integrations capture customer intent and populate CRM directly; Knowledge Base AI ingests vendor documentation for automatic response generation. Used by Rappi, EF, Dentalia, and Addi. Treble positions against Wati (similar WhatsApp specialist with broader geography), ManyChat WhatsApp (Instagram-DM-first competitor), Yalo (LATAM enterprise WhatsApp), Sirena (regional CS focus), Charles (DACH-focused), and Respond.io (multi-channel chat with WhatsApp). The differentiator is BSP status + LATAM brand traction since 2019.', 'https://treble.ai', 'paid', '[]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Drag-and-drop chat flow builder","AI chatbots — FAQs, lead qualification, conversation summary","Bulk campaign broadcasting with audience segmentation","Live agent handoff with escalation rules","Native HubSpot + Salesforce CRM integration","Knowledge Base AI — auto-ingest vendor docs for responses","Official Meta WhatsApp Business API (BSP Partner)","Multi-language support (Spanish, Portuguese, English)","Quality-monitoring + conversation analytics"}', '{"HubSpot","Salesforce","Meta WhatsApp Business API","Google Sheets"}', true, '{"LATAM and Spanish-speaking ecommerce / consumer brands","B2C operators where WhatsApp is the dominant customer-comms channel","Companies needing official BSP-status sender (vs unverified API access)","Mid-market brands with HubSpot or Salesforce as system of record"}', '{"US-only or English-only markets where Wati / Respond.io fit better","Instagram-DM-first creators (ManyChat is the right tool)","DACH / European-only operators (Charles is regionally focused)","Buyers wanting transparent public pricing before sales conversation"}', 'The default WhatsApp marketing platform for LATAM brands in 2026 — Treble''s official Meta BSP partner status, native CRM hooks, and proven traction with Rappi-tier customers make it the natural pick for Spanish-speaking-market ecommerce. The Knowledge Base AI auto-response feature is genuinely useful for support-heavy WhatsApp deployments. It''s weaker than Wati on global geographic coverage, weaker than Respond.io on cross-channel orchestration, and the no-public-pricing posture is friction. Pick Treble when LATAM is the primary market; skip if your customers don''t live on WhatsApp.', now()),

-- ── spiky-ai → business-finance ─────────────────────────────
('Spiky.ai', 'spiky-ai', 'AI sales coaching and meeting intelligence — real-time call scoring, live coaching, and MEDDPICC playbook adoption tracking.', 'Spiky.ai is an AI-powered sales coaching and meeting intelligence platform that combines real-time guidance during calls with post-meeting analytics to improve rep performance and close rates. The product''s distinguishing thesis is "scale winning behaviors": identify what top reps do, codify it into the playbook, and surface that guidance to every rep in real time during calls — rather than after-the-fact coaching reviews. Real-time call scoring monitors momentum during active meetings; live coaching surfaces playbook guidance and suggested objection responses mid-call; call analysis evaluates talking speed, tone, and methodology adherence (MEDDPICC, BANT); team playbook adoption tracking flags reps with execution gaps; deal pipeline visibility surfaces progression metrics; personalized rep coaching ties to a training library and skill-acceleration tools; CRM sync writes to existing sales stack. Spiky.ai positions against Gong (revenue intelligence incumbent, post-call-heavy), Chorus (similar coaching depth, ZoomInfo-owned), Demodesk (consolidation play across recording + coaching + CRM sync), Avoma (meeting intelligence + scheduling), Fathom (recorder-first), and Wingman (acquired by Clari, less standalone now).', 'https://www.spiky.ai', 'paid', '[]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Real-time call scoring with live momentum monitoring","Live coaching with playbook guidance + objection responses","Call analysis — talking speed, tone, methodology adherence","MEDDPICC + BANT playbook execution tracking","Deal pipeline visibility with progression metrics","Personalized rep coaching with training library","CRM sync to existing sales stack","Team-level playbook adoption analytics","Skill-acceleration tools tied to call performance"}', '{"Salesforce","HubSpot","Microsoft Teams","Google Meet","Zoom","Microsoft Outlook","Google Calendar","Slack"}', true, '{"Mid-market sales teams running structured methodology (MEDDPICC, BANT)","Sales managers wanting real-time coaching, not after-the-fact reviews","Teams with established top performers whose behaviors should scale","Sales orgs already on Salesforce or HubSpot wanting CRM-native coaching"}', '{"Solo sellers and 1-2 person sales teams (overkill for low call volume)","Pure transcription-only workflows (Otter / Fireflies cheaper)","Teams that don''t use a structured sales methodology (coaching has no anchor)","Buyers needing transparent public tier pricing"}', 'The real-time coaching pick in the AI sales meeting category — Spiky.ai''s live mid-call momentum scoring + playbook guidance differentiate against Gong and Chorus, which lean post-call analytics. The MEDDPICC adoption tracking is genuinely useful for managers running structured methodology. It''s weaker than Gong on enterprise revenue-intelligence depth, weaker than Demodesk on the bundled CRM Concierge story, and the demo-only sales motion (no public pricing) is friction. Pick Spiky.ai when in-call coaching matters more than retrospective deal review; skip if Gong-grade analytics is the actual requirement.', now()),

-- ── smartli → marketing-seo ─────────────────────────────────
('Smartli', 'smartli', 'AI content + visual creation for ecommerce — product descriptions, ad copy, blog posts, and image editing for dropshipping.', 'Smartli is an AI-powered content and visual-creation suite built for ecommerce entrepreneurs and dropshippers. The product combines copywriting tools (product descriptions, blog posts, ad copy) with image-editing capabilities (background removal, watermark removal, photo enhancement) to support the full Shopify-store launch and growth motion. Product Description Generator outputs high-converting copy in one click; AI Blog Writer produces SEO-optimized blog posts; AI Ads Writer generates paid-ad copy for Facebook and other channels; Background Remover isolates subjects for clean product photos; Watermark Remover strips logos from sourced imagery; Photo Enhancer boosts image quality for storefront use. Pricing covers Pro and Empire plans (both under $100/mo) plus a 7-day free trial. Shopify is the primary integration listed. Smartli positions against AdCreative.ai (ad-creative specialist with broader feature surface), Pencil (AI ad creative for performance marketing), Copy.ai (general-purpose AI writing), Jasper (enterprise content marketing AI), and Predis.ai (social-content specialist).', 'https://smartli.ai', 'freemium', '[{"plan":"Free Trial","price":"7-day free trial","features":["No hidden charges","Full feature access during trial"]},{"plan":"Pro","price":"Under $100/mo (exact $ not surfaced)","features":["Recommended for startups","Product Description Generator","AI Blog Writer","AI Ads Writer","Image editing tools"]},{"plan":"Empire","price":"Under $100/mo (exact $ not surfaced)","features":["Advanced features beyond Pro","All copy + image tools"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web"}', '{"AI product description generator","AI blog writer (SEO-optimized)","AI ads writer (Facebook + multi-channel)","Background remover","Watermark remover","Photo enhancer","Multi-language content support","Shopify-first integration","One-click bulk product description generation"}', '{"Shopify"}', true, '{"Dropshipping operators on Shopify needing fast bulk product descriptions","Ecommerce entrepreneurs without copywriter or designer budget","Side-hustle store owners launching first product catalog","Sourcing-heavy stores needing watermark removal on supplier images"}', '{"Performance-marketing teams needing AdCreative.ai-grade ad creative depth","Content marketers needing Jasper-grade brand voice and editorial workflow","WooCommerce / BigCommerce / Magento stores (Shopify-only integration)","Buyers wanting precise public pricing (homepage hides exact tier $)"}', 'The default cheap-and-cheerful ecommerce content pick for Shopify dropshippers in 2026 — Smartli bundles product descriptions, ad copy, blog posts, and image-editing under $100/mo, which is materially cheaper than running AdCreative + Copy.ai + a separate background remover. The Shopify-first integration removes integration friction. It''s weaker than AdCreative.ai on ad-creative quality and Performance-Max-grade variants, weaker than Jasper on brand-voice consistency at scale, and the Shopify-only integration locks out other carts. Pick Smartli when budget matters and you''re on Shopify; skip otherwise.', now()),

-- ── closely → business-finance ──────────────────────────────
('Closely', 'closely', 'AI LinkedIn + email outreach automation — multichannel sales engagement with built-in personalization and account safety.', 'Closely is an AI-powered LinkedIn + email outreach platform that combines safe LinkedIn automation (smart limits, human-like timing) with multichannel sales engagement and AI-personalized messaging at scale. The product covers LinkedIn DM automation with account-safety guardrails, AI-powered message personalization, a unified inbox for LinkedIn DMs, InMails, and email replies, a LinkedIn email finder with verified contact enrichment, multi-team campaign analytics, and orchestrated multichannel sequences combining LinkedIn touches with email follow-ups. The differentiator vs the LinkedIn-automation category is the explicit account-safety posture — human-like timing patterns and smart per-day limits to avoid LinkedIn flagging, paired with AI personalization that doesn''t read as templated. Closely positions explicitly against HeyReach (similar LinkedIn-first multichannel), Expandi (LinkedIn automation veteran), Lemlist (email-first multichannel with LinkedIn add-on), Apollo (database-first sequencing platform), and Clay (data-enrichment-first), and lighter against Lemlist (email-first multichannel), Reply.io (sales-engagement suite with LinkedIn module), La Growth Machine (LinkedIn + email with similar positioning), and Dux-Soup (older LinkedIn automation).', 'https://www.closelyhq.com', 'paid', '[]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Safe LinkedIn automation with smart limits and human-like timing","AI-powered message personalization at scale","Unified inbox — LinkedIn DMs + InMails + email replies","LinkedIn email finder with verified contact enrichment","LinkedIn outreach analytics across campaigns + teams","Multichannel campaign orchestration (LinkedIn + email)","Account-safety guardrails to avoid LinkedIn flagging","Team-level campaign visibility and reporting","Verified email enrichment from LinkedIn profile data"}', '{"HubSpot","Salesforce","Pipedrive","GoHighLevel","LinkedIn"}', true, '{"Outbound SDR teams running LinkedIn-first prospecting at scale","Founders and small sales teams without time to manage LinkedIn manually","Agencies running outreach for multiple clients across LinkedIn + email","Sales teams already on HubSpot / Salesforce wanting CRM-native LinkedIn data"}', '{"Volume-first cold email shops where LinkedIn isn''t a primary channel","Solo users wanting cheap one-off LinkedIn scraping (Phantombuster fits)","Buyers needing transparent public pricing before signup","B2C / consumer outbound where LinkedIn isn''t the right channel"}', 'A solid LinkedIn-first multichannel outreach pick when account safety matters as much as message volume — Closely''s human-like timing and smart per-day limits are explicitly designed against LinkedIn''s flagging algorithms in a way faster competitors aren''t. The unified DM + InMail + email inbox is genuinely useful for SDRs juggling channels. It''s weaker than HeyReach on raw LinkedIn-account scaling, weaker than Lemlist on email-first multichannel polish, weaker than Apollo on database breadth, and the no-public-pricing posture is friction. Pick Closely when LinkedIn is your primary channel and you''ve been flagged before.', now()),

-- ── typewise → customer-support ─────────────────────────────
('Typewise', 'typewise', 'AI Agent Platform for customer service — multi-agent orchestration, omnichannel resolution, success-based pricing at $1 per resolution.', 'Typewise is an AI Agent Platform for customer service that automates support workflows through intelligent multi-agent orchestration. The product handles ticket resolution, knowledge retrieval, and system actions across CRM / ERP / billing / ITSM with explicit hybrid intelligence — AI escalates to humans when confidence drops or policy requires it. Natural-language workflow definition lets non-technical teams build automation in plain English without coding. Omnichannel delivery covers email, chat, WhatsApp, social, voice, and ChatGPT / Claude integration; multilingual support handles any language in / out; automated evaluations + simulation validate changes before live deployment to prevent regressions; the Knowledge & Actions Hub reads / writes across CRM, ERP, billing, ITSM, and 200+ native integrations plus 6,000+ Model Context Protocol (MCP) connectors. Pricing is success-based at $1 per resolution — no traditional monthly tiers. Typewise positions against Decagon (similar AI customer-service agent platform), Sierra (Bret Taylor''s AI agent company), Ada (CS automation incumbent), Intercom Fin (in-product AI), and Forethought (CS automation specialist). Note: Typewise pivoted from earlier "AI typing assistant" positioning into enterprise CS agent automation in 2024–2025.', 'https://typewise.app', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Resolution-Based","price":"$1 per resolution","features":["Success-based pricing — pay only for resolved tickets","Multi-agent orchestration","Omnichannel (email, chat, WhatsApp, social, voice)","200+ native integrations + 6,000+ MCP connectors","Hybrid intelligence with human escalation","Automated evaluations + simulation","Multilingual any-in / any-out","15-minute deployment"]}]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Multi-agent orchestration for CS workflows","Natural-language workflow definition (no coding)","Omnichannel — email, chat, WhatsApp, social, voice, ChatGPT, Claude","Multilingual support (any language in / out)","Hybrid intelligence with human escalation policies","Automated evaluations + simulation before live deployment","Knowledge & Actions Hub across CRM / ERP / ITSM / billing","200+ native integrations","6,000+ Model Context Protocol (MCP) connectors","Success-based $1/resolution pricing model"}', '{"Salesforce Service Cloud","Zendesk","Freshdesk","Microsoft Outlook","Gmail","Microsoft Teams","Slack","WhatsApp"}', true, '{"Mid-market and enterprise CS teams automating high-volume ticket resolution","Multilingual support orgs needing any-language inbound + outbound","Companies on Salesforce Service Cloud or Zendesk wanting deeper AI than native","Teams that prefer per-resolution pricing over per-seat or per-message models"}', '{"Sub-1K-ticket/month operations (overhead exceeds savings)","Buyers wanting in-product AI tightly bound to one suite (Intercom Fin fits)","Solo founders or small teams without an existing CS workflow to automate","Companies wanting AI typing assistance for individual writing (Typewise pivoted away from that)"}', 'The success-based AI customer-service agent platform for mid-market teams that have outgrown bolt-on AI inside Zendesk or Salesforce Service Cloud and want a real multi-agent orchestrator. Typewise''s $1/resolution pricing aligns vendor incentive with customer outcome better than seat-based competitors. It''s weaker than Decagon on enterprise pedigree, weaker than Sierra on agent-design ergonomics, and the recent pivot from typing-assistant means brand recognition is mid-flight. Pick Typewise when you want resolution-aligned pricing and 200+ integration breadth; skip if you need an in-product CS suite (Intercom Fin) or are sub-1K-tickets/month.', now())

